Vice President Mike Pence hosted Prime Minister of Greece Alexis Tsipras for a meeting at the White House. They discussed the strong ties between the United States and Greece and congratulated Greece on its return to economic growth. The Vice President encouraged further reforms to spur investment and reiterated U.S. support for debt relief. They expressed a desire to deepen cooperation in the economic and security spheres, including the visit of a high-level delegation to the 2018 Thessaloniki International Fair. They also discussed Greece's role as a pillar of stability in the region and reaffirmed their support for the Euro-Atlantic integration of Turkey and the countries of the Western Balkans. The Vice President expressed support for a comprehensive settlement to reunify Cyprus and welcomed Greece's increasing cooperation with Israel, Cyprus, and Egypt in the eastern Mediterranean.